race.comment: CINSAULT (4) resumes for a top Sydney barn and when last seen capped two heavily bet placings with a spacious Maiden win at Kembla Grange, backed off the map. Has the early speed to clear the awkward barrier, and his lead-up trials suggest she'll return even better. OCTA DE LAGO (6) resumed at Hawkesbury and charged from the back beaten a whisker. He has more to give and the top hoop rides from an inside gate. He can sit closer and fitter is a live chance. TACT (3) resumed at Newcastle in solid order and is proven second-up. He has more up his sleeve and will get every chance positioning forward. TITANIUM MISS (2) has to push forward from a wide barrier but can't be ruled out back in grade. His best would see him very competitive.
